Now let me look at the `buildTestSearchLabwareByHint` in the FixtureRunner:

```typescript
function buildTestSearchLabwareByHint() {
  return async (_hint: string): Promise<Array<{ recordId: string; title: string }>> => [];
}
```

It returns an empty array! So when `resolve_labware` calls `searchLabwareByHint("96-well plate")`, it gets no matches, and the code falls through to the "zero matches" case:

```typescript
if (matches.length === 0) {
